reviews.review_text: Sweet show! A really nice high quality recording of a fine performance. I remember it feeling like it was going to be a good night right away with the Help>Slip>Franklin's opening that really got everyone going.  Check out the So Many Roads and the audience reaction to Jerry's singing at the end.  These 2 shows at Copps are definately worth a listen. The ride back to Long Island in the snowstorm with a rented Volvo was another story - but we made it. Great memories. Thanks for posting this!
Best Road Trip Wanna Go? Hell yeah!. Left Purdue University in West Lafayette,IN. Amazing Road trip with two other GD buds. Terrapin and US Blues will always bring a smile from this show!
